Derrick Spies, Correspondent Zodwa Francisco Mnguni, 51, from Y section, Asibambe in Umlazi has been missing since Wednesday. (Supplied) Multimedia    ·   User Galleries   ·   News in Pictures
	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Police have appealed to the community to assist them in locating a 51-year-old woman from Y section, Asibambe Place in Umlazi. Police spokesperson, Colonel Thembeka Mbhele said Zodwa Francisco Mnguni had been reported missing by her daughter, who told police she had been missing since Wednesday. Mbhele said they did not have a description of the clothes she had been wearing at the time, and all her belongings, including her cellphone, were found in her room. He said anyone with information on her whereabouts could contact Captain NC Ndimande on 031 909 9967 or 082 350 0843, or they could contact the national Crime Stop number on 08600 10111.  Zodwa Francisco Mngun (Supplied)  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  